Popularized by the ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' sketch "[[Wayne's World]]", '''schwing''' is a [[slang]] term used as an exclamation of excitement or appreciation for the female form (example: "You've just won the lottery!" "''Schwing!''"). In essence, the term is used to represent the act of achieving an [[erection]]. The term is an [[onomatopoeia]] of the sound a [[sword]] makes when drawn from a metal [[scabbard]].

It should not be confused with "schwingen," the [[German language|German]] word for "to swing."

Schwing is also an [[Irish language|Irish Gaelic]] colloquialism of appreciation for the male form; it is surprisingly inappropriate to use it about the female form.

Schwing also used as a word for a good looking woman 

Schwing is also a trademarked brand name of concrete pumps manufactured in Germany and [[White Bear Lake, MN]] ([http://www.schwing.com www.schwing.com]).

